&lt;p&gt;I believe that you are not capturing the right params from the code you have posted. So in your repository you are looking for &lt;code&gt;startDate&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;endDate&lt;/code&gt;
but the url in question has &lt;code&gt;from_date=2018-01-12&amp;amp;to_date=2018-03-03&lt;/code&gt;. I believe it should be;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;$from_date = Carbon::parse(request('from_date'))-&amp;gt;startOfDay();
$to_date = Carbon::parse(request('to_date'))-&amp;gt;endOfDay();
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PS: By the way you are using a custom action of &lt;code&gt;searchProjects()&lt;/code&gt; in your ProjectsController. Its a best practice that you would create an invokable class i.e. single action controller ( if thats the only action you require ) and then have your logic there. so may be something like below;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;// Route
Route::get('search_projects', Project\SearchProjectsController::class)

// Controller
class SearchProjectsController extends Controller 
{
    public function __invoke(Request $request)
    {
       // your logic
    }
}
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

